(firstQuint)Selegiline Transdermal System for the Treatment of Cocaine Dependence - 1.

 The study objectives are to assess the efficacy and safety of the Selegiline Transdermal System (STS) in reducing cocaine use in subjects with cocaine dependence.

 It is hypothesized that selegiline treatment compared to placebo, will be associated with fewer days of cocaine use as assessed by self-report confirmed with urine assays for benzoylecgonine (BE).

